  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Night-Eating Syndrome (NES) is an eating disorder characterised by excessive eating at
      night, sleep disturbance and morning anorexia. This 12-week study examines the effect of
      escitalopram on symptoms of NES.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
