  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Night Eating Questionnaire</measure>
    <time_frame>baseline, 12 weeks</time_frame>
    <safety_issue>No</safety_issue>
    <description>The Night Eating Questionnaire (NEQ) is a 14-item self-report scale designed to assess the symptoms of NES including nocturnal ingestions, evening hyperphagia, morning anorexia, and mood/sleep. Scores range from 0-56, with higher scores indicative of greater severity. The NEQ has an acceptable internal consistency reliability (.70). A cut-score of 25 has been shown to yield a positive predictive value of .62.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
